  return soydata.VERY_UNSAFE.ordainSanitizedHtml(guide.render(soy.$$augmentMap(opt_data, {content: soydata.VERY_UNSAFE.$$ordainSanitizedHtmlForInternalBlocks('<h3>' + soy.$$escapeHtml(opt_data.page.title) + '</h3><h6>' + soy.$$escapeHtml(opt_data.page.description) + '</h6><article id="1"><h2>Dependencies</h2><p>The following external software dependencies are necessary to correctly run some commands:</p><p>a) <a href="https://git-scm.com/">Git</a> (download for <a href="https://git-scm.com/download/linux">Linux</a>, <a href="https://git-scm.com/download/mac">macOS</a>, <a href="https://git-scm.com/download/win">Windows</a>)</p><p>b) <a href="https://www.docker.com/">Docker</a> (download for <a href="https://docs.docker.com/engine/installation/linux/">Linux</a>, <a href="https://download.docker.com/mac/stable/Docker.dmg">macOS</a>, <a href="https://download.docker.com/win/stable/InstallDocker.msi">Windows</a>)</p><p>Docker version 1.12.0 or later is required. If you use macOS, install the Docker for Mac. If you use Windows, please install Docker for Windows. Docker Toolbox, still available for earlier Mac and Windows systems is not supported.</p></article><article id="2"><h2>Installing</h2><p>If you use a Unix-like system such as macOS or Linux open your Terminal and run:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('curl https://cdn.wedeploy.com/cli/latest/wedeploy.sh -sL | bash'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>If you use Windows, you probably want the <a href="https://bin.equinox.io/c/8WGbGy94JXa/cli-stable-windows-amd64.msi">Windows amd64 installer</a>. For other systems, check a list of <a href="https://dl.equinox.io/wedeploy/cli/stable">all builds available</a>.</p><p><strong>Check your docker configuration:</strong> docker comes with a 2.0GB maximum memory limit by default on macOS and Windows. You should increase this limit to at least 4.0GB.</p></article><article id="3"><h2>Creating projects locally</h2><p>You are able to organize your services by project. Inside each project you can create services (called containers here), like static hosting, data API, Auth service, etc.</p><p>Use <code>we create</code> to create projects and containers. You can create a project anywhere on your machine. Containers might be created one directory above a project for your convenience.</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('Usage:\n    we create --project <projectID> --container <serviceID>'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '</article><article id="4"><h2>Running projects locally</h2><p>For this demo we are going to use the hosting boilerplate.</p><ol><li>Start local infrastructure:</li>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we run'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<li>Clone this repository:</li>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('git clone https://github.com/wedeploy/boilerplate-hosting.git\ncd boilerplate-hosting'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<li>Link this container to a new project named demo:</li>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we link --project demo'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<li>Now your container should be accessible from <a href="http://hosting.demo.wedeploy.me">hosting.demo.wedeploy.me</a></li></ol><p><em>The first time you run the project it might take a few minutes while the hosting image is being downloaded in the background.</em></p></article><article id="5"><h2>Remotes and friendly host style</h2><p>Many commands requires <code>--project</code>, <code>--container</code>, or <code>--remote</code> flags. You can use the following patterns for passing these values:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we <command> --project <projectID> --container <serviceID>'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>and the friendly host style:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we <command> <serviceID>-<projectID>.<remote address>'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>or even</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we <command> <serviceID>-<projectID> --remote <remote>'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>For the local cloud, just don\'t add a <code>--remote</code> or <code>&lt;remote address&gt;</code> value like in:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we log public.chat'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>or to list all logs by containers on the project &quot;chat&quot;:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we log chat'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>Remotes can be managed in a similar fashion as git\'s remote command:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('$ we remote -v\nwedeploy        wedeploy.io'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>If you know how to use <code>git remote</code> you already know how to use <code>we remote</code>.</p><p>For your convenience we include the wedeploy cloud remote by default once you log in on the CLI app with <code>we login</code> (requested when necessary).</p><p>All commands that support <code>--project</code>, <code>--container</code>, and / or <code>--remote</code> support this host style as well.</p></article><article id="6"><h2>Fetching project and container logs</h2><p>You can fetch projects and container logs with</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we log --project <projectID> --container <serviceID>'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>or with a friendly host style like</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we log <serviceID>-<projectID>.wedeploy.me'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<h5>Examples:</h5><p>See the logs for the last 20min for the data container on the wechat project:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we log --project wechat --container data --since 20min'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>Watch for logs on the hosting container on the demo project:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we log hosting.demo.wedeploy.me --watch'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '</article><article id="7"><h2>Listing projects and containers</h2><p>Watch the listing of all projects running locally:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we list --watch'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>List all your projects running on the WeDeploy cloud:</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we list wedeploy.io'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '<p>or</p>' + ElectricCode.render({code: soydata.$$markUnsanitizedTextForInternalBlocks('we list --remote wedeploy'), mode: 'xml'}, null, opt_ijData) + '</article><h2>What\'s next?</h2><ul><li>Learn more about using <a href="/docs/intro/using-the-api-client.html">the WeDeploy API Client</a>.</li></ul><input type="hidden" value="' + soy.$$escapeHtmlAttribute(opt_data.page.title) + '"><input type="hidden" value="' + soy.$$escapeHtmlAttribute(opt_data.site.title) + '">')}), null, opt_ijData));
